Karaage

Ingredients (Serves 2)

Chicken and Marinade
	•	350 g (12 oz) chicken thigh, boneless, skin-on, cut into ~4 cm pieces
	•	30 ml (2 tbsp) soy sauce
	•	10 g (2 tsp) fresh ginger, finely grated
	•	6 g (1 tsp) garlic, finely grated

Coating and Frying
	•	60 g (about 1/2 cup) potato starch
	•	600 ml (2 1/2 cups) neutral oil (canola or rice bran), for frying

⸻

Method
	1.	Marinate
Combine chicken, soy sauce, ginger, and garlic. Massage thoroughly until evenly coated. Rest 15 minutes in the refrigerator.
	2.	Prepare for Frying
Remove chicken from marinade. Lightly blot with paper towels so the surface is damp but not wet.
	3.	Heat Oil and Coat
Heat oil to 170°C (340°F). Dredge chicken in potato starch immediately before frying, shaking off excess for a thin, even coating.
	4.	First Fry
Fry chicken in batches for about 3 minutes, until the crust sets and the exterior is pale golden. Remove to a wire rack and rest 3 minutes.
	5.	Second Fry
Increase oil temperature to 180°C (355°F). Return chicken to oil and fry 60–75 seconds until deeply golden, crisp, and rigid.
	6.	Drain and Serve
Transfer to a wire rack to drain briefly. Serve hot.

⸻

Optional Refinements
	•	Add a few drops of toasted sesame oil to the marinade for subtle nutty depth
	•	Finish with a light dusting of sansho pepper for aromatic bitterness
	•	Serve with lemon wedges on the side for restrained acidity